Description: Distributed AtomSpace for OpenCog Hyperon
 The Distributed AtomSpace (DAS) is an extension of OpenCog Hyperon's
 Atomspace designed to facilitate multiple simultaneous connections with
 diverse AI algorithms.
 .
 Key features:
  - Distributed hypergraph knowledge base
  - Query engine with cognitive optimization
  - Attention broker for resource allocation
  - Evolution, link creation, and inference agents
  - Integration with Hyperon MeTTa
  - Support for multiple DBMS backends (MongoDB, Redis, PostgreSQL, Mork)

Package: das-dev
Architecture: all
Depends: das (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Development files for Distributed AtomSpace
 Development headers, libraries, and tools for building applications
 that integrate with the Distributed AtomSpace.
